<Project>

  <!--
    Benzene's Azure Functions trigger source generator emits the [Function] trigger classes. The
    Functions SDK's worker-indexing source generators (metadata + executor) run in the same
    compilation and cannot see another generator's output, so a generated [Function] would be listed
    in functions.metadata (produced by the post-compile reflection task, which DOES see it) yet be
    invisible to the worker's generated executor - a host/worker mismatch. Disabling worker indexing
    falls back to the reflection-based metadata AND executor, both of which see generated code, making
    the generated triggers work end to end.

    Set only when the app hasn't chosen a value, so it stays overridable. Flows transitively to any app
    referencing a Benzene.Azure.Function.* package (all reference Core). Repo examples use
    ProjectReferences, which don't process buildTransitive, so they set the property in their csproj.
  -->
  <PropertyGroup>
    <FunctionsEnableWorkerIndexing Condition="'$(FunctionsEnableWorkerIndexing)' == ''">false</FunctionsEnableWorkerIndexing>
  </PropertyGroup>

</Project>
